Business Brief -- Kyocera Corp.:
   Japanese Ceramics Maker
   Revises Earnings Projections
Kyocera now expects a 40.7 billion yen pretax profit on an
unconsolidated basis, or for the parent company alone. Last
November the company predicted a 21% pretax profit drop to
44.1 billion yen.
   Net profit is expected to mark a 24% fall from the year
earlier to 22.5 billion yen, down from November's forecast of
24.0 billion yen. Kyocera's sales forecast was revised to
317.5 billion yen, or a 4% year-on-year drop, from 331
billion yen predicted in November.